# pyenv
#   For a library or binary, you wish to ignore these files by default
#   For a managed Python environment, you may wish to check them in
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#1173, it is a recommended practice to check in Pipfile.lock.
#   However, in case you don't want it, feel free to uncomment the next line.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to check in poetry.lock in applications.
#   For a library, it should be ignored.
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to check in pdm.lock in applications.
#   For a library, it should be ignored.
#pdm.lock

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/pdm-project/pdm
__pypackages__/

